HEADWORD: Diisatogen
<hw>Di`i*sat"o*gen</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Pref.
<ets>di-</ets> + <ets>isat</ets>ine + <ets>-gen</ets>.]</ety>
<fld>(Chem.)</fld> <def>A red crystalline nitrogenous substance of
artificial production, which by reduction passes directly to
indigo.</def>⟦br⟧
